The command should have worked, and that is sometimes a clue.
1) There are parts of tidyverse that are attached if tidyverse is installed and attached, and then there are parts that are not. You can find this in the documentation or ask someone like ChatGPT "what parts of tidyverse require a separate library() command and which ones work with only library(tidyverse)?"

2) Sometimes I have working code that suddenly does not work. Try making sure that all packages are using the latest version.


